sec.p:
Patients included in this study met the following criteria:
Preoperative CBCT examination to determine that the teeth were osseous-embedded supernumerary teeth;
Embedded teeth affecting normal eruption of permanent teeth;
Orthodontic treatment requiring extraction or causing odontogenic cysts;
No systemic diseases and contraindications to tooth extraction.

Patients with the following conditions were excluded:
Have sprouted extra teeth;
Have contraindications of anesthesia;
Pregnant or lactating women;
Patients are unable to cooperate due to mental illness or other reasons, with poor compliance
